{
  "texts": [
    "Yapp et al.",
    "introduced the BFEL framework in [186], which employs blockchain technology to reduce communication overhead by decentralizing the aggregation process.",
    "Meanwhile, Zhu et al.",
    "proposed Delayed Gradient Averaging (DGA) in [187] to mitigate high communication latency by pipelining communication with computation.",
    "Another method called FedPM [188] addresses the challenge of high communication costs in federated learning by freezing weights at initial random values and learning to sparsify the random network."
  ]
}